0th.270: Nicole Rood reacts after telling how she survived a tornado by holding onto the door handle of a house as she was lifted off the ground in the 6400 block of West Cowden Rd., Saturday, June 16, 2019 near Ellettsville, Ind. Rood's boyfriend Brett Cantrell survived by hanging onto a tree across the road. The couple were in their car when the storm stuck. The tornado destroyed several homes, tore up trees, and left dangerous live power lines scattered around the area.
